Class Relationship

java.lang.Object
org.example.scdpro2.business.models.BClassDiagarm.Relationship
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Relationship extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a relationship between two BClassBox objects in a class diagram. The Relationship class defines the connection between a source and a target class box, including details such as the relationship type, multiplicities, and a label for the relationship. This class supports serialization for persistence.

  • Field Details

    • source

      public BClassBox source
      The source BClassBox in the relationship. This is the class that the relationship originates from.

    • target

      public BClassBox target
      The target BClassBox in the relationship. This is the class that the relationship points to.

    • type

      public final RelationshipLine.RelationshipType type
      The type of the relationship (e.g., association, inheritance). This field indicates the kind of connection between the source and target classes.

    • sourceMultiplicity

      public String sourceMultiplicity
      The multiplicity of the source class in the relationship (e.g., "1", "0..*", "1..*"). This field defines how many instances of the source class can participate in the relationship.

    • targetMultiplicity

      public String targetMultiplicity
      The multiplicity of the target class in the relationship (e.g., "1", "0..*", "1..*"). This field defines how many instances of the target class can participate in the relationship.

    • relationshipLabel

      public String relationshipLabel
      The label associated with the relationship. This field is used to store additional information or a name for the relationship.

      Constructs a new Relationship object with the specified source, target, relationship type, multiplicities, and label. It initializes the relationship between two BClassBox objects with the given details.
      Parameters:
      source - The source class box of the relationship.
      target - The target class box of the relationship.
      type - The type of the relationship (e.g., "association", "inheritance").
      sourceMultiplicity - The multiplicity of the source class.
      targetMultiplicity - The multiplicity of the target class.
      relationshipLabel - The label for the relationship.
